<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 13:01:14 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>人体细胞可以通过微小的管子相互传递 DNA——这就是它如何促进癌症的生长</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-cells-can-pass-dna-to-each-other-through-tiny-tubes-heres-how-it-may-fuel-cancer-growth</link><description>了解 DNA 如何在通过形成纳米管连接的两个细胞之间交换，并了解为什么这对于癌症研究至关重要。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/human-cells-can-pass-dna-to-each-other-through-tiny-tubes-heres-how-it-may-fuel-cancer-growth.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 13:01:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-cells-can-pass-dna-to-each-other-through-tiny-tubes-heres-how-it-may-fuel-cancer-growth</guid></item><item><title>Teclistamab 可延长复发性骨髓瘤的缓解期，18 个月时 70% 的患者无进展</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/teclistamab-extends-remission-in-relapsed-myeloma-with-70-progression-free-at-18-months</link><description>根据 2019 年发表的一项主要国际 III 期临床试验的结果，接受免疫疗法 teclistamab 治疗的复发性多发性骨髓瘤患者比接受标准疗法的患者寿命显着更长，且缓解时间也更长。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/teclistamab-extends-remission-in-relapsed-myeloma-with-70-progression-free-at-18-months.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 12:46:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/teclistamab-extends-remission-in-relapsed-myeloma-with-70-progression-free-at-18-months</guid></item><item><title>生物样本库科学：在室温下储存细胞</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/biobanking-science-storing-cells-at-room-temperature</link><description>最近的一项研究表明，冷冻干燥和室温生物库不会影响培养的人类细胞中的 RNA 质量。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/biobanking-science-storing-cells-at-room-temperature.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 12:31:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/biobanking-science-storing-cells-at-room-temperature</guid></item><item><title>小鼠冻干精子长期室温保存的方法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/method-for-long-term-room-temperature-storage-of-mouse-freeze-dried-sperm</link><description>镰田 Y.、山路 K.、牛込 N. &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/method-for-long-term-room-temperature-storage-of-mouse-freeze-dried-sperm.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 12:16:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/method-for-long-term-room-temperature-storage-of-mouse-freeze-dried-sperm</guid></item><item><title>实验室培育的大脑类器官为生物计算机提供动力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/lab-grown-brain-organoids-power-biocomputers</link><description>由理学硕士 Simon Spichak 撰写的一篇专题报道研究了 Cortical Labs 和 FinalSpark 等生物技术公司如何利用人类脑细胞到电极，执行计算功能并测试细胞对电和化学刺激的反应。为了制造生物计算机，科学家们在硬件外壳的多电极阵列顶部培养类器官（在本例中为神经组织的小球体），然后可以将其用于从测试药物到玩视频游戏等各种用途。该工作发表在《医学互联网研究杂志》上。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/lab-grown-brain-organoids-power-biocomputers.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 12:01:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/lab-grown-brain-organoids-power-biocomputers</guid></item><item><title>IceCube检测到宇宙中微子光谱的断裂，排除了简单的幂律模型</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/icecube-detects-break-in-cosmic-neutrino-spectrum-ruling-out-simple-power-law-model</link><description>一项新研究&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/icecube-detects-break-in-cosmic-neutrino-spectrum-ruling-out-simple-power-law-model2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 11:46:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/icecube-detects-break-in-cosmic-neutrino-spectrum-ruling-out-simple-power-law-model</guid></item><item><title>“向月球射击？”研究人员表示，目标要低一些</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/shoot-for-the-moon-aim-a-bit-lower-researchers-say</link><description>你应该有多大的野心？民间智慧提供了相互矛盾的建议：“向月球射击”，但也“不要让完美成为优秀的敌人。”怀俄明大学、斯坦福大学和科罗拉多大学博尔德分校的研究人员进行的一项新研究使用数学模型表明，野心处于中间位置——高于平均水平，但有限。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/shoot-for-the-moon-aim-a-bit-lower-researchers-say.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 11:31:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/shoot-for-the-moon-aim-a-bit-lower-researchers-say</guid></item><item><title>触角星系内可能潜伏着一个隐藏的超大质量黑洞</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-hidden-supermassive-black-hole-may-be-lurking-inside-the-antennae-galaxies</link><description>天文学家可能在著名的触角星系 NGC 4038/4039 内发现了一个隐藏的超大质量黑洞，这对碰撞星系以其壮观的恒星形成爆发而闻名。概述调查结果的论文已发布到&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-hidden-supermassive-black-hole-may-be-lurking-inside-the-antennae-galaxies2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 11:16:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-hidden-supermassive-black-hole-may-be-lurking-inside-the-antennae-galaxies</guid></item><item><title>金刚石量子传感器可以揭示难以捉摸的交变磁体</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/diamond-quantum-sensor-could-reveal-elusive-altermagnets</link><description>近一个世纪以来，已知的磁铁有两种。铁磁体是经典的磁铁，可以吸引金属并将图片粘在冰箱上。反铁磁体在原子尺度上隐藏了它们的磁性，但因其技术潜力而日益受到重视。过去十年中发现的第三类可能结合了两者的最佳品质。它们被称为交替磁铁，有朝一日可以帮助制造更快、更节能的电子产品。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/diamond-quantum-sensor-could-reveal-elusive-altermagnets.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 11:01:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/diamond-quantum-sensor-could-reveal-elusive-altermagnets</guid></item><item><title>多通道量子霍尔超导器件中出现拓扑态</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/topological-states-emerge-in-quantum-hall-superconductor-devices-with-multiple-channels</link><description>拓扑相是物质的不寻常状态，它产生受材料整体结构（即“拓扑”）保护的特性，而不是微观细节。这些相对于量子技术的发展非常有意义，因为它们可以产生理想的电子特性，并且能够抵抗缺陷和干扰。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/topological-states-emerge-in-quantum-hall-superconductor-devices-with-multiple-channels2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 10:46:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/topological-states-emerge-in-quantum-hall-superconductor-devices-with-multiple-channels</guid></item></channel></rss>